Article I Definitions
Except as otherwise specified, the following terms as used herein will be construed to have the following scope and meaning:
1.1 "Assigns" means the Facility Owner and its respective successors and assigns.
1.2 "Base Gas" means the Gas required to remain in the storage cavern of the Storage Facility in order to protect the cavern's integrity.
1.3 "Bcf" means one billion (1,000,000,000) cubic feet.
1.4 "Btu" means one British Thermal Unit, and shall be the quantity of heat required to raise the temperature of one (1) pound of water from fifty-eight and five-tenths degrees (58.5 degrees) to fifty-nine and five-tenths degrees (59.5 degrees) Fahrenheit. MMBtu means one million (1,000,000) Btus. The terms "MMBtu" and "Dekatherm" shall be used synonymously.
1.5 "Business Day" means Monday through Friday from 8:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. Central Clock Time, as adjusted, when appropriate, for changes from Standard to Daylight Savings Time, and vice versa, excluding United States Federal Banking Holidays.
1.6 "Company" means Enterprise Texas Pipeline LLC.
1.7 "Contract Year" means the twelve (12) Month period beginning on the effective date of the storage service agreement and each subsequent twelve-month period thereafter during the term of the agreement.
1.8 A cubic foot of Gas equals the volume of Gas that occupies one cubic foot at a temperature of 60 degrees Fahrenheit, a pressure of 14.73 Psia, and dry. Mcf means one thousand (1,000) cubic feet and MMcf means one million (1,000,000) cubic feet.
1.9 "Customer" means the party that holds all lawful right and/or title to the Gas that is being stored and who executes a storage service agreement with Company.
1.10 "Electronic Data Interchange" or "EDI" means electronic communication that complies with the Electronic Delivery Mechanism Standards of the North American Energy Standards Board and its successors.
1.11 "Electronic" or "electronically" shall mean data communication between Company and Customer or vice versa through StarWeb, Company's scheduling and electronic communications service, or via EDI.
1.12 "Facility Owner" means RFC Caverns, L.P., formerly known as ILI Caverns, Inc., also formerly ML Caverns, Inc.
1.13 "FERC" or "Commission" means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission or any successor agency.
1.14 "Firm" means storage service that has the highest priority of storage service offered by Company.
1.15 "Fuel" means the quantity of Gas for Company use, line loss, and other unaccounted-for quantities in the Storage Facility.
1.16 "Gas" means natural gas in its natural state, produced from wells, including casinghead gas produced with crude oil, natural gas from gas wells and residue gas resulting from processing both casinghead gas and gas well gas.
1.17 "Gas Day" means a period of consecutive hours, beginning at 9:00 a.m. and ending at 9:00 a.m. the following day (Central Clock Time).
1.18 "Interruptible" means storage service that is subject to interruption at any time by Company, without liability as set forth herein, and shall have the priority specified in Article V of this Statement of Operating Conditions.
1.19 "Intraday Nomination" means a nomination submitted to Company after the timely nomination deadline and before the Intraday Nomination deadline as forth herein for quantities of Gas which will be scheduled for receipt and/or delivery on the Gas Day of flow.
1.20 "Maximum Daily Delivery Quantity" or "MDDQ" means the maximum quantity of Gas, expressed in MMBtu, specified in Customer's storage service agreement that Customer may nominate and receive and that Company shall deliver at a Point of Delivery at relatively constant hourly rates of flow over the course of such Gas Day.
1.21 "Maximum Daily Injection Quantity" or "MDIQ" means the maximum quantity of Gas, expressed in MMBtu, specified in Customer's storage service agreement that Customer may nominate and that Company shall receive at the Point of Receipt for injection into storage each Gas Day at constant hourly rates of flow over the course of such Gas Day (excluding Fuel).
1.22 "Maximum Daily Receipt Quantity" or "MDRQ" means the maximum quantity of Gas, expressed in MMBtu, specified in Customer's storage service agreement that Customer may nominate and deliver and that Company shall receive at a Point of Receipt at relatively constant hourly rates of flow over the course of such Gas Day.
1.23 "Maximum Daily Withdrawal Quantity" or "MDWQ" means the maximum daily withdrawal quantity of Gas, expressed in MMBtu, specified in Customer's storage service agreement that Customer may nominate and that Company shall withdraw from storage and tender to Customer at Point(s) of Delivery each Gas Day at constant hourly rates of flow over the course of such Gas Day.
1.24 "Maximum Storage Quantity" or "MSQ" means the volume of capacity, expressed in MMBtu, in Company's facilities located in Wharton County, Texas that Customer has available for its use pursuant to its storage service agreement with Company.
1.25 "MAOP" means Maximum Allowable Operating Pressure.
1.26 "Month" means the period beginning at 9:00 a.m. Central Clock Time on the first Gas Day of a calendar month and ending at 9:00 a.m. Central Clock Time on the first Gas Day of the next succeeding calendar month.
1.27 "Overrun" means any quantity that is in excess of Customer's MDDQ, MDIQ, MDWQ, or MSQ as set forth in Customer's storage service agreement. "Authorized Overrun" means an Overrun that is nominated by Customer and approved and scheduled by Company. "Unauthorized Overrun" means an overrun that Company does not approve and schedule for service.
1.28 "Point(s) of Delivery" means the point or points located at the Storage Facility and specified in Customer's storage service agreement at which Company shall tender Gas to Customer.
1.29 "Point of Receipt" means the point located at the Storage Facility and specified in Customer's storage service agreement at which Company shall receive Gas from Customer.
1.30 "Psia" means pounds per square inch absolute.
1.31 "Psig" means pounds per square inch gauge.
1.32 "StarWeb" shall mean Company's scheduling system and electronic communications system.
1.33 "Storage Facility" means the underground natural gas storage caverns and associated facilities located in Wharton County, Texas, which the Company leases and operates and in which Company has storage rights.
1.34 "Transporter" means the Customer's transporter designated to deliver Gas to the Point of Receipt or Customer's transporter designated to receive Gas from the Point(s) of Delivery.
1.35 "Working Gas Inventory" means the quantity of Gas in MMBtu, that Customer has in place in the Storage Facility for Customer's account, provided that the Working Gas Inventory shall never exceed Customer's Maximum Storage Quantity.
1.36 "Transportation" shall mean the contractual movement of Gas from Point(s) of Receipt to Point(s) of Delivery, whether by forward haul, backhaul, displacement or exchange.
Article II Services and Operating Provisions
2.1 Firm Storage Service ("FSS")
2.1.1 Subject to the operating conditions of the Transporter and the Storage Facility, Company shall receive Gas for injection from Customer at the Point of Receipt and deliver Gas to Customer at the Point(s) of Delivery as scheduled by Customer from time to time. Company's Firm storage services shall include the following, except as provided for in Article V (Priority & Interruption of Service) and Article XVII (Force Majeure):
(i) Injection of Customer's Gas per Customer's nomination up to Customer's MDIQ provided that injection of such Gas would not cause Customer to exceed its MSQ, that Customer delivers the nominated quantity plus Fuel reimbursement to the Point of Receipt, and that Customer's daily injection for each point of receipt shall not exceed Customer's MDRQ. If Customer's Working Gas Inventory at the beginning of any Gas Day is more than 50% of Customer's MSQ, then Customer's MDIQ shall be limited as stated in Customer's storage service agreement.
(ii) Withdrawal of Customer's Gas and delivery of such Gas to the Point(s) of Delivery per Customer's nomination up to Customer's MDWQ, provided that Customer has sufficient Gas in its Working Gas Inventory and provided that Customer's daily withdrawal for each Point of Delivery shall not exceed Customer's MDDQ.
(iii) Storage of Gas in amounts up to Customer's MSQ.
2.1.2 Company shall not be obligated on any Gas Day to inject Gas into storage, withdraw Gas out of storage, or store Gas for Customer in excess of Customer's MDIQ, MDWQ, or MSQ, respectively. However, Customer may request to make injections in excess of its MDIQ and withdrawals in excess of its MDWQ. Such a request by Customer shall be submitted to Company by nomination, and shall be received by Company in accordance with the nomination and scheduling provisions as set forth in this Statement of Operating Conditions. In the event that Customer makes such a request, Company will authorize the Overrun to the extent Company determines, in its sole discretion, that additional injection or withdrawal flexibility exists during the time period of the request and in accordance with Article V (Priority and Interruption of Service).
2.2 Interruptible Services
Subject to the operating conditions of the Transporter and the Storage Facility and subject to the MSQ, MDIQ, and MDWQ as stated in Customer's service agreement, Company may perform Interruptible Storage Services provided that the provision of such services does not prevent Company from meeting all of its Firm obligations and maintaining the operational integrity of the storage facility. Interruptible Services are available provided Company has determined in its sole discretion that it has sufficient operationally available Base Gas, storage capacity, withdrawal capacity and injection capacity to perform the requested service. Company's Interruptible Storage services shall include the following, except as provided for in Article V (Priority & Interruption of Service) and Article XVII (Force Majeure):
2.2.1 Interruptible Storage ("IS")
Company's Interruptible Storage Service shall include the following:
(i) Injection of Customer's Gas per Customer's nomination up to Customer's MDIQ provided that injection of such Gas would not cause Customer to exceed its MSQ and that Customer delivers the nominated quantity plus Fuel reimbursement to the Point(s) of Receipt.
(ii) Withdrawal of Customer's Gas and delivery of such Gas to the Point(s) of Delivery per Customer's nomination up to Customer's MDWQ provided that Customer has sufficient Gas in its Working Gas Inventory.
(iii) Storage of Gas in amounts up to Customer's MSQ.
2.2.2 Interruptible Deferred Delivery Service ("IDS")
IDS shall include the following:
(i) Injection of Customer's Gas per Customer's nomination and the delivery schedule set forth in the service agreement, provided such Gas would not cause Customer to exceed its MDIQ, unless otherwise agreed to by Company, and that Customer delivers the nominated quantity plus Fuel reimbursement to the Point(s) of Receipt.
(ii) Withdrawal of Customer's Gas per Customer's nomination and the redelivery schedule set forth in the service agreement, provided such Gas would not cause Customer to exceed its MDWQ, unless otherwise agreed to by Company, and that Customer receives the nominated quantity at the Point(s) of Delivery.
(iii) Storage of Customer's Gas in amounts up to Customer's MSQ for an agreed upon period of time set forth in the service agreement.
(iv) If Company, upon nomination by Customer, fails to schedule quantities of Gas for delivery to Customer within the planned delivery schedule, Company will implement a revised delivery schedule as soon as practicable. Additionally, Customer will not incur any penalties for Company's failure to schedule quantities nominated.
(v) If Customer fails to withdraw quantities of Gas set out in the delivery schedule or a revised delivery schedule pursuant to Paragraph 2.2.2(iv), Customer shall be subject to penalties as set forth in service agreement and the quantity of Gas remaining in storage may be cashed out under terms specified in the service agreement.
2.2.3 Interruptible Advancing Service ("IAS")
IAS shall include the following:
(i) Withdrawal of advanced (loaned) Gas at the Point(s) of Delivery per Customer's nomination and the delivery schedule set forth in the service agreement up to Customer's MDWQ, unless otherwise agreed to by Company.
(ii) Injection of the redelivered Gas per Customer's nomination and the redelivery schedule set forth in the service agreement, provided such Gas would not cause Customer to exceed its MDIQ, unless otherwise agreed to by Company, and that Customer redelivers the nominated quantity plus Fuel reimbursement to the Point(s) of Receipt.
(iii) If Company, upon nomination by Customer, fails to schedule quantities of Gas for redelivery to Company within the planned redelivery schedule, Company will implement a revised redelivery schedule as soon as practicable. Additionally, Customer will not incur any penalties for Company's failure to schedule quantities nominated.
(iv) If Customer fails to redeliver quantities of Gas set out in the redelivery schedule or a revised redelivery schedule pursuant to Paragraph 2.2.3(iii), Company may purchase replacement Gas and Customer shall pay Company the cost of the replacement Gas, which includes the actual cost of replacement supplies and any costs or penalties incurred by Company or its Customers as a result of Customer's failure to redeliver replacement Gas, plus all other costs incurred by Company to secure such replacement Gas, including, but not limited to, third-party marketing fees, Transportation, and all other costs for securing replacement Gas. Customer may also be subject to penalties as set forth in the service agreement.
2.2.4 Interruptible Wheeling Service ("IWS")
IWS shall consist of the following:
(i) Company's Interruptible Wheeling Service shall consist of the Transportation of Gas, on an interruptible basis, by Company for Customer on Company's storage header system between agreed upon Point(s) of Receipt and Point(s) of Delivery.
(ii) Receipt of Customer's Gas per Customer's nomination, provided such Gas would not cause Customer to exceed its MDRQ and that Customer delivers the nominated quantity plus Fuel reimbursement to the Point(s) of Receipt.
(iii) Delivery of Customer's Gas to the Point(s) of Delivery per Customer's nomination, provided such Gas equals the amount of Gas Customer delivered to the Point(s) of Receipt less Fuel reimbursement.
2.2.5 Title Transfer Service ("TTS")
TTS shall consist of the following:
(i) Customer may sell all or a portion of its Working Gas Inventory to any other Customer with which Company has a storage service agreement if:
(ii) Both purchaser and seller of the Working Gas Inventory provide Company with verification of the transfer in writing; and
(iii) The purchase does not cause either Customer to exceed its MSQ, as specified in the Customer's storage service agreement; and
(iv) If title to seller's Gas was held under a NGPA Section 311 (A) (2) agreement, then purchaser of such Gas must transfer title to a NGPA Section 311 (A) (2) storage service agreement or if the title to seller's Gas was held under an intrastate storage service agreement, then purchaser of such Gas must transfer title to an intrastate storage service agreement.
(v) Company will recognize the transfer for purposes of computing available Working Gas Inventory and applicable Maximum Daily Injection Quantities and Maximum Daily Withdrawal Quantities on a prospective basis within 24 hours after receiving the written verification.
2.3 For all services, Customer shall tender or cause to be tendered to Company at the Point of Receipt any Gas which Customer desires to have injected into storage plus applicable Fuel volumes. Customer shall also receive or cause to be received Gas requested to be withdrawn from storage at the Point(s) of Delivery.
2.4 Company shall not be obligated to receive Gas for injection, or to withdraw Gas from storage, on an hourly basis at rates of flow in excess of 1/24 of Customer's MDIQ or MDWQ.
2.5 If Customer has multiple storage service agreements with Company, Customer shall not be permitted to combine injection, storage or withdrawal services available under such storage service agreements. Specifically, Gas injected under a particular storage service agreement must be stored and withdrawn under that same storage service agreement. Further, separate storage service agreements must be executed for NGPA Section 311 service and intrastate service if both such services are so desired, and separate storage service agreements must be executed for Firm and Interruptible service if both such services are so desired.
Article III Laws and Regulations
3.1 Company's storage services are subject to all present and future valid laws and lawful orders of all regulatory authorities now or hereafter having jurisdiction of the services or facilities used to provide such services, including, without limitation, the provisions of Subpart C of Part 284 of the Commission's Regulations. Should Customer or Company, by force of any such law or regulation imposed at any time during the term of Customer's storage service agreement, be rendered unable, wholly or in part, to carry out its obligations under the storage service agreement, other than to make payments due hereunder, the storage service agreement nevertheless shall continue and shall be deemed modified to conform with the requirements of such law or regulation, except as hereinafter provided. The storage service agreement shall be modified to the least extent necessary to conform to such requirements; the primary intent of any such modification being to retain, to the greatest extent possible, the bargain of the Customer's storage service agreement. The storage service agreement is expressly made subject to any and all tariff and other rate filings made by Company and approved by any federal or state regulatory body as such may be amended from time to time. Company shall have the right to propose to the FERC or other governing regulatory body such changes in its rates and terms of service at any time as it deems necessary, and Customer's storage service agreement shall be deemed to include any changes which are made effective pursuant to order or regulation or provisions of law, without prejudice to Customer's right to protest the same. In the event that any regulatory body having jurisdiction over the storage service agreement prohibits Company from collecting specific rates for the services provided under the storage service agreement or subjects its storage facilities to any greater or different regulation or jurisdiction, by order or otherwise, than that existing on the date of initial storage of Gas hereunder (or thereafter as such regulation or jurisdiction may have changed and been accepted), then Company shall have the right to terminate the storage service agreement on the effective date of such greater or different regulation or jurisdiction, anything herein to the contrary notwithstanding and shall have no liability to Customer or any other entity in connection with any such termination other than withdrawal of Customer's Gas.
Article IV Request for Service Agreement
4.1 A service agreement is required for all services hereunder and shall be subject to all terms and provisions of this Statement of Operating Conditions. Any potential customer wishing to obtain storage services from Company on a Firm or Interruptible basis, including extensions of existing services, shall submit in writing to Company a request for storage service in substantially the same format as that shown in Exhibit 1. Customer shall provide information requested by Company if necessary to adequately examine Customer's request for service agreement. Such request for service agreement may be delivered in person or submitted by United States mail, overnight courier service, email or fax. If Company and the potential customer mutually agree to the rates that the potential customer will pay for storage service, then Company shall, subject to the execution of a storage service agreement, endeavor to provide service within the time specified in the written request. The potential customer's request for service agreement shall be considered complete only if the information specified in Paragraph 4.2 is provided in writing.
Requests for service may be sent to: Enterprise Texas Pipeline LLC 1100 Louisiana Street Houston, TX 77002-5227 Attn: Transportation and Storage Marketing Phone: (713) 381-2522 Fax (713) 381-8300
4.2 Each request for service shall include the following information:
4.2.1 Potential customer's name, address, representative, telephone number, fax number, and e-mail address, if available.
4.2.2 For NGPA Section 311 storage service, a statement indicating the "on behalf of" entity(ies) the Customer warrants meets the provisions of Section 284 of the Commission's regulations.
4.2.3 Type of service requested (Firm or Interruptible, and type of Interruptible) and quantities for each of the following:
(i) Maximum Storage Quantity (stated in MMBtu) (ii) Maximum Daily Withdrawal Quantity (stated in MMBtu/day) (iii) Maximum Daily Injection Quantity (stated in MMBtu/day)
4.2.4 For Firm service only, Point(s) of Delivery and MDDQ (MMBtu/day) for each Point of Delivery.
4.2.5 Price offered by potential customer for each service requested (Dollars per MMBtu).
4.2.6 Term of service, including the date service is requested to commence and the date service is requested to terminate.
4.2.7 Acceptance of a request for service agreement is contingent upon a satisfactory credit appraisal by Company. To enable Company to conduct such credit appraisal, potential customer shall submit the information set out in Paragraphs (i) through (iii) below; provided, however, that submission of such material shall not be deemed acceptance of a request for service by Company, which determination shall be made by Company only after submission of the material and information set forth below and a determination by Company that potential customer is sufficiently creditworthy. Company shall apply consistent evaluation practices on a nondiscriminatory basis to determine creditworthiness.
(i) Potential customer must provide (a) a copy of its most recent audited financial statement; (b) a bank reference; and (c) at least three trade references, which indicate that potential customer's obligations are being paid on a prompt basis. Such documents shall be provided to:
Enterprise Texas Pipeline LLC c/o Credit Department 1100 Louisiana Street, Suite 15.76 Houston, TX 77002-5227 Telephone: (713) 381-6836 Fax: (713) 381-2813
In the event potential customer cannot provide the information above, then potential customer shall, if applicable, provide that information for its parent company.
(ii) Company shall not be required to perform or to continue any storage service on behalf of any potential customer or Customer who is or has become insolvent; who fails to meet payment obligations in accordance with Paragraphs 20.2, 20.3, and 20.4 of Article XX, or who, at Company's request, fails within a reasonable period to demonstrate creditworthiness. Provided, however, such potential customer or Customer may receive storage service if it prepays for such service, provides a standby irrevocable letter of credit, or furnishes an acceptable guarantee by another person or entity which satisfies the credit requirements of Company, in an amount equal to three (3) months or the duration of the potential customer's bid or Customer's storage service agreement, whichever is shorter, of charges calculated on a one hundred percent (100%) load factor basis and other applicable charges.
(iii) For purposes herein, the insolvency of a potential customer or Customer shall be conclusively demonstrated if a potential customer or Customer or any parent entity thereof (hereinafter collectively referred to as "the Customer") makes an assignment or any general arrangement for the benefit of creditors; files a petition or otherwise commences, authorizes or acquiesces in the commencement of a proceeding or cause under any bankruptcy or similar law for the petition of creditors or has such petition filed against it and such proceeding remains undismissed for thirty (30) days; otherwise becomes bankrupt or insolvent (however evidenced); liquidates a substantial part of its property or affairs; or is generally unable to pay its debts as they become due. (iv) Company may reassess the creditworthiness of and performance by Customer from time to time; and Customer shall be required to demonstrate creditworthiness and/or provide adequate assurances of performance throughout the term of the executed service agreement. A Firm Customer shall provide Company a copy of Customer's audited annual financial report each year. 4.3 Service requests by potential customers for Firm storage service shall be processed on a first-come first-served basis. That is, requests for Firm storage shall be allocated to the first potential customer offering to pay a rate for storage service and offering a contract term that Company finds acceptable and the execution of a service agreement.
4.4 Company shall have the right to reject any request for service agreement that:
4.4.1 Does not contain the required information set forth herein;
4.4.2 Company, in Company's sole opinion, is operationally unable to perform without detriment to its system or to the rights of existing Customers on its system;
4.4.3 Requires Company to construct facilities to effectuate the receipt or delivery;
4.4.4 Requires Company to perform a service that, in Company's sole opinion, may be contrary to any existing law or regulation or creates a potential safety or environmental hazard.
Company shall have no liability to Customer or any other entity in connection with such rejection.
4.5 Company shall have the right to waive the informational requirements of Paragraphs 4.1 and 4.2 on a not unduly discriminatory basis provided that Customer has previously satisfied the requirements of this Article and Company does not require such information to process the Request for Service in accordance with the provisions of this Statement of Operating Conditions and all applicable laws and regulations.
Article V Priority and Interruption of Service
5.1 Any Customer executing a storage service agreement with Company shall be entitled to the injection, storage, and withdrawal of Gas, subject to the availability of storage capacity, injection, and deliverability in the following order of declining priority:
5.1.1 Firm Storage Service
5.1.2 Interruptible Storage Services
5.1.3 Authorized Overrun injections or withdrawals
5.1.4 Make-up volumes to correct prior variances between (i) Transporter and Company, (ii) Customer and Company, and (iii) Customer and Transporter if the variance was due to Company's failure to receive or deliver Customer's scheduled volumes.
5.2 In the event Company is unable to receive or deliver volumes for any reason and determines, in its sole discretion, it is unable to meet the scheduled obligations to Customers, Company will interrupt storage service to Customers in the reverse order of priority set forth in Paragraph 5.1. If Firm service must be interrupted, interruption of storage service to Firm Customers shall be pro rata based on MSQ, MDIQ, and/or MDWQ, as applicable. Interruption of storage service to Interruptible Customers shall be based on the storage service charges paid by the Customers, with the lowest rate being interrupted first. Any ties for Interruptible service shall be interrupted on a pro rata basis.
5.3 To the extent Interruptible storage capacity which is being utilized by an Interruptible Customer is needed by Company in order to satisfy Company's obligations to Firm Customers, Company shall request that Interruptible Customers withdraw all, or any portion of, the Interruptible quantities held in storage, according to the priorities set forth in Paragraph 5.2. Upon such a request, Customer shall nominate for withdrawal the maximum amount possible every day until the requested capacity is made available. If any Customer fails to withdraw such storage Gas, then Company may take, free and clear of any adverse claims, title to such Gas in storage inventory; provided, however, that if Customer was unable to withdraw its Gas due to an interruption of Customer's withdrawal service during that twenty-four (24) hour period, Customer shall be allowed to withdraw its Gas within a reasonable time period following such interruption.
5.4 Company shall provide customers as much advance notice as is practicable under the circumstances of any interruption.
5.5 Company shall not be liable for any loss or damage to any person or property caused, in whole or in part, by any interruption or curtailment of service, except to the extent caused by Company's gross negligence or willful misconduct. Customer agrees to indemnify and hold harmless Company, its officers, agents, employees, and contractors from and against any and all suits, claims, liability, loss, damages, costs (including attorneys' fees and court costs) or encumbrances whatsoever brought by any person or entity against Company as a result of or arising out of any interruption or curtailment of service hereunder for Customer (unless caused by Company's gross negligence or willful misconduct).
Article VI Point(s) of Receipt and Delivery
6.1 Customer shall tender all Gas for injection into storage to Company at the Point of Receipt as specified in Customer's storage service agreement. The quantity of Gas tendered by Customer to Company for injection into storage shall not exceed the MDIQ plus the applicable Fuel, without the consent of Company.
6.2 Company shall tender all Gas to be withdrawn from storage to Customer at the Point(s) of Delivery as specified in Customer's storage service agreement. The quantity of Gas delivered to Customer (i) shall not exceed the MDWQ at all Point(s) of Delivery, without the consent of Company and (ii) for Firm service only, shall not exceed the MDDQ at each Point of Delivery.
6.3 Customer shall be responsible for Transportation from the Point(s) of Delivery and payment of all Transportation charges relating thereto. Customer shall be responsible for Transportation to the Point of Receipt and payment of all Transportation charges relating thereto.
Article VII Pressure and Injection /Withdrawal Rates
7.1 Company shall deliver Gas to Customer at pressures sufficient to enter the pipeline facilities at the Point(s) of Delivery against the operating pressures maintained by Transporter. Company shall not be required to deliver Gas at pressures in excess of those required by Transporter or in excess of Transporter's maximum allowable operating pressure (MAOP), not to exceed 1200 Psig. Customer shall deliver or cause to be delivered to Company all Gas for injection at the Point of Receipt at pressures not less than 850 Psig and not in excess of the MAOP of Company's facilities at the Point of Receipt. Company shall be responsible for maintaining facilities at such Point of Receipt to permit Customer to deliver Gas to Company at such allowed pressures. Transporter and/or Company is under no obligation to install additional facilities to permit the entry of Customer's Gas into the Storage facility.
7.2 The Storage Facility is designed to store, inject and withdraw Gas based on "normal" operating pressures maintained by the Transporter at the Point(s) of Receipt/Delivery with allowances for reasonable fluctuations. In the event that conditions on the Transporter's system vary substantially from this "normal" design condition coincident with high levels of Customer receipt or delivery activity, Company's capability to receive or deliver the quantities set forth in its storage service agreements may be impaired, resulting in an interruption in service. If this happens, capacity will be allocated pursuant to Article V.
Article VIII Title and Risk of Loss
8.1 Customer warrants for itself, its successors and assigns, that it will have at the time of delivery of Gas at the Point(s) of Receipt for storage hereunder either good title or all rights necessary and appropriate to have the Gas stored. Article XIII Measurement
13.1 The unit of volume for measurement of Gas received and delivered hereunder is one thousand (1,000) cubic feet of Gas at a base temperature of sixty (60) degrees Fahrenheit and at an absolute pressure of fourteen and seventy-three hundredths (14.73) Psia. The MMBtu equivalent of such unit of volume shall be determined by multiplying each such unit of volume by the total heating value per cubic foot of Gas hereunder and by dividing the result by one thousand (1,000).
13.2 All measurement facilities hereunder shall be installed and operated in accordance with the standards approved by the American National Standards Institute of June 28, 1977, and prescribed in the Gas Measurement Committee of the American Gas Association ("AGA") Report Number 3 (ANSI/API 2530-92; API#14.3; GPA 8185-92), as it is now and from time to time may be revised, amended or supplemented. In the event electronic measurement is utilized, the installation and operation shall conform to AGA Part No. 8/API21.1 as it is now and may from time to time be revised, amended, or supplemented. Gas quantities measured with the use of ultrasonic meters shall be determined in accordance with the provisions of the Gas Measurement Committee of the AGA Report No. 9, as it is now and may from time to time be revised, amended or supplemented. 13.3 Company will arrange for the ownership and operation of the measuring stations located at the Point of Receipt and Point(s) of Delivery. The changing of charts or collection of electronic measurement data and the calculation of the volume and energy value (MMBtu) thereof shall be the responsibility of Company. The calibrating and adjusting of meters shall be performed or arranged for by Company in compliance with Paragraph 13.8.
13.4 Customer has the right to be present at the time of any installing, reading, cleaning, changing, repairing, inspecting, testing, calibrating or adjusting done in connection with the equipment used in measuring Gas hereunder. The records from such measuring equipment shall remain the property of Company or its representative, but upon request, Company shall submit to Customer copies of the records and charts, together with calculations therefrom, subject to their return within thirty (30) days after receipt thereof. If Customer fails to return the records and charts within thirty (30) days, Company shall be under no obligation to provide additional records and charts until the non-returned records and charts are returned to Company. Company shall retain the charts for a period of two (2) Contract Years following the end of the Contract Year to which they are applicable. Company shall give Customer sufficient notice in advance of all tests so that Customer may, at its election, be present in person or by its representative to observe adjustments, if any, which are made.
13.5 For the purposes of measurement and meter calibration, the atmospheric (barometric) pressure shall be assumed, unless otherwise determined by the Standard Gas Measurement Law, to be constant, determined by elevation and specific site location irrespective of variations in actual atmospheric pressure from time to time.
13.6 The temperature of the Gas hereunder shall be determined by the continuous use of a recording thermometer. The temperature recorded each Gas Day, during periods of flow only, shall be used in computing the Gas volume for that Gas Day.
13.7 At the sole option of Company, Btu and relative density may be determined by means of an on-line chromatograph, a portable chromatograph, a continuous sample, or a spot sample taken at the Points of Receipt and Points of Delivery. In the event a continuous or spot sample is utilized, the results of the analysis of such sample may be applied to Gas delivered on the first Gas Day of the following Month and thereafter until the first Gas Day of the Month following in which another sample is taken. For the Month in which Gas first flows, the results of the analysis of such continuous or spot sample shall also be used in calculating quantities of Gas for the Month in which the test is made. Fractional analysis shall be performed in accordance with ANSI/ASTM D3588-79 as is now in effect and from time to time may be amended, revised, or updated.
13.8 If, upon any test, the metering equipment at any point is found to be inaccurate in the aggregate by one (1) percent or more, registration thereof and any payment based upon such registrations shall be corrected at the rate of such inaccuracy for any period of inaccuracy which is definitely known or agreed upon, or if not known or agreed upon, then for a period extending back one-half (1/2) of the time elapsed since the Gas Day last calibrated not to exceed fifteen (15) Gas Days. Following any test, any metering equipment found to be inaccurate to any degree shall be adjusted immediately to measure accurately. If, for any reason, any meter is out of service or out of repair so that the quantity of Gas delivered or redelivered through such meter cannot be ascertained or computed from the readings thereof, the quantity of Gas so delivered during the period such meter is out of service or out of repair shall be estimated and agreed upon by the parties hereto on the basis of the best available data, using the first of the following methods that is feasible:
13.8.1 by using the registration of any check measuring equipment of the other party, installed and registering; or
13.8.2 by correcting the error if the percentage of error is ascertainable by calibration, test or mathematical calculation; or
13.8.3 by estimating the quantity of receipts or deliveries from preceding periods under similar conditions when the meter was registering accurately.
Article XIV Balancing and Penalties
14.1 In the event that Company or Customer delivers or causes to be delivered to Transporter at the Point(s) of Receipt or Delivery a quantity of Gas not equal to the quantity of Gas received or taken by Customer or Company, a "Transportation Imbalance" may occur. Provided that Company has taken or delivered the quantity of Gas nominated by Customer and scheduled by Transporter, Customer shall be liable for all imbalances under its Transportation agreement with Transporter. Upon notification by Customer or Transporter that a Transportation Imbalance exists because Company failed to deliver or receive the quantity of Gas nominated by Customer and scheduled by Transporter, Company will endeavor to correct the Transportation Imbalance subject to any restrictions imposed by Transporter but Company shall be solely responsible and liable for any charges, penalties, costs and expenses incurred or payable by either party as a result of the Transportation Imbalance. Customer agrees to use its best efforts to prevent or diminish any occurrences of imbalances.
14.2 Customer shall hold Company harmless for all costs and penalties which may be assessed by Transporter under Customer's Transportation agreement with Transporter, unless the costs and penalties are due to the negligence of Company. Customer and Company shall cooperate with each other and with the Transporter to verify delivery and receipt of the volumes of Gas delivered hereunder on a timely basis.
14.3 A Customer shall be liable for and shall be required to reimburse Company for all penalties, charges and fees which Company is required to pay to Transporter as a consequence of Customer's actions. The recovery of such penalty amounts shall be on an as-billed basis.
Article XV Rates and Charges
15.1 Company has elected to perform NGPA Section 311 Transportation services utilizing the rates approved by the FERC pursuant to Section 284.123(b)(2)(i) of the Commission's regulations. Company's approved rates for storage services are market-based.
15.2 Subject to modifications that may be imposed and/or authorized by any regulatory body having jurisdiction, each month Customer shall, where applicable as specified in Customer's storage service agreement, pay Company the following amounts for Firm storage service:
(a) Withdrawal Reservation Charge. A monthly charge multiplied by each MMBtu of Customer's Maximum Daily Withdrawal Quantity.
(b) Capacity Reservation Charge. A monthly charge multiplied by each MMBtu of Customer's Maximum Storage Quantity.
(c) Overrun Service Charge. In the event that Customer receives authorization to overrun its MDIQ or MDWQ pursuant to Article II, Customer shall be subject to the applicable overrun injection charge per MMBtu or overrun withdrawal charge per MMBtu as specified in Customer's storage service agreement.
(d) Fuel Reimbursement. The amount of Gas for Fuel determined in accordance with Article XIX.
15.3 Subject to modifications that may be imposed and/or authorized by any regulatory body having jurisdiction, each month Customer shall pay Company the negotiated amounts for Interruptible storage service, plus Fuel reimbursement as applicable, as specified in Customer's Interruptible storage service agreement
Article XVI Nominations and Scheduling
16.1 Company's Gas Scheduling Department may be contacted by Customer as follows:
Schedulers: Contacts and telephone numbers are posted on StarWeb and on company's web site at www.starwebgas.com Business Hours Telephone: (7:30 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.) (713) 381-4634 (After 5 p.m. and Weekends) (713) 381-7904 After Hours Emergency Telephone: (800) 644-4773 (Gas Control - Houston, Texas) Gas Scheduling Department's Fax Number: (713) 381-8299
16.2 Customer shall complete and execute the StarWeb Electronic Communications Services Client Authorization Form and receive approval from Company prior to submitting electronic nominations to Company. If Customer desires to submit nominations to Company via EDI, Customer must sign an Electronic Data Interchange Trading Partner Agreement prior to submitting nominations via EDI.
16.3 During any Gas Day when Customer desires Company to inject or withdraw Gas, Customer shall submit a nomination to Company's Gas Scheduling Department electronically through StarWeb or by EDI. The portal address for StarWeb is www.starwebgas.com. Company may at its sole discretion allow Customer to submit a nomination via fax.
16.4 Customer shall submit to Company a nomination which shall include, at a minimum:
(i) Customer name and storage service agreement number; and
(ii) Daily quantity of Gas to be injected at the Point of Receipt or withdrawn at the Point(s) of Delivery (expressed in MMBtu); and
(ii) Customer-defined begin dates and end dates; and
(iv) Contracts with upstream and downstream connected parties.
In the event Customer has more than one storage service agreement, Customer shall provide Company with separate nominations for each storage service agreement. Customer shall specify in writing the order in which Gas received and/or delivered by Company shall be applied to such service agreements at the Point(s) of Delivery and/or Point(s) of Receipt.
All nominations, excluding Intraday Nominations, shall have rollover options during each Month. Specifically, Customers shall have the ability to nominate for several Gas Days in a given Month, up to and including the last Gas Day of the specific Month, provided the nomination begin and end dates are within the term of Customer's contract. Such nominations shall be deemed "Standing Nominations." Customer shall provide as a component of its nomination such information as may be required by Company to enable it to identify, confirm, and schedule the nomination. Customer shall request Overrun quantities in a separate nomination.
16.5 Company will utilize the following nomination cycles:
(i) THE TIMELY NOMINATION CYCLE (CYCLE 1) - NOMINATIONS FOR GAS FLOWING THE FOLLOWING GAS DAY OR THEREAFTER
Nomination: 11:30 a.m. (CCT) Customer's nomination received by Company;
Confirmation: 3:30 p.m. (CCT) Completed confirmations received by Company from upstream and downstream-connected parties;
Notice: 4:30 p.m. (CCT) Company provides notice of scheduled quantities to Customer via StarWeb;
Scheduling: Scheduled quantities resulting from the timely nomination cycle shall be effective at 9:00 a.m. (CCT) for the Gas Day of flow.
(ii) THE EVENING NOMINATION CYCLE (CYCLE 2) - NOMINATIONS FOR GAS FLOWING THE FOLLOWING GAS DAY
Nomination: 6:00 p.m. (CCT) Customer's nomination received by Company;
Confirmation: 9:00 p.m. (CCT) completed confirmations received by Company from upstream and downstream-connected parties;
Notice: 10:00 p.m. (CCT) Company provides notice of scheduled quantities to Customer via StarWeb including notice of any reduced quantities, if applicable. Bumping is permitted during the Evening Nomination Cycle;
Scheduling: Scheduled quantities resulting from Evening Nomination Cycle shall be effective at 9 a.m. for the Gas Day of flow.
(iii) THE INTRADAY 1 NOMINATION CYCLE (CYCLE 3) - NOMINATIONS FOR GAS FLOWING THE SAME GAS DAY:
Nomination: 10:00 a.m. (CCT) Customer's nomination received by Company;
Confirmation: 1:00 p.m. (CCT) Completed confirmations received by Company from upstream and downstream-connected parties;
Notice: 2:00 p.m. (CCT) Company provides notice of scheduled quantities to Customer via StarWeb including notice of any reduced quantities, if applicable. Bumping is permitted during the Intraday 1 Nomination Cycle;
Scheduling: Scheduled quantities resulting from Intraday 1 Nomination Cycle shall be effective at 5:00 p.m. (CCT) during the Gas Day of flow.
(iv) THE INTRADAY 2 NOMINATION CYCLE (CYCLE 4) - NOMINATIONS FOR GAS FLOWING THE SAME GAS DAY:
Nomination: 5:00 p.m. (CCT) Customer's nomination received by Company;
Confirmation: 8:00 p.m. (CCT) Completed confirmations received by Company from upstream and downstream-connected parties;
Notice: 9:00 p.m. (CCT) Company provides notice of scheduled quantities to Customer via StarWeb including notice of any reduced quantities, if applicable. Bumping is not allowed during the Intraday 2 Nomination Cycle;
Scheduling: Scheduled quantities resulting from Intraday 2 Nominations shall be effective at 9:00 p.m. (CCT) on the Gas Day of flow.
16.6 Company may, in its sole discretion, accept nominations at such later times as operating conditions permit or establish alternative nomination timelines, upon confirmation that corresponding upstream and downstream arrangements in a manner satisfactory to Company have been made. Company will first schedule nominations received in accordance with the timelines set forth in Paragraph 16.5. Company will then determine if it will accept and schedule nominations after the applicable nomination deadline.
16.7 All Standing Nominations shall remain in place for the duration of the Month until changed by Customer with a new nomination. New nominations to replace Standing Nominations must be received by Company's Gas Scheduling Department in accordance with the scheduling timelines set out in Paragraphs 16.5 and 16.6.
16.8 If Customer submits to Company an Intraday Nomination or a new nomination replacing a Standing Nomination, and Company does not receive confirmation of the newly nominated quantities from the upstream or downstream connected parties, Company shall schedule the lesser of 1) the newly nominated quantity or 2) the quantity confirmed with upstream or downstream connected parties.
16.9 Requests to amend previously scheduled nominations may be accepted during the Gas Day according to the timelines set forth in Paragraph 16.5 (iii and iv), subject to operational conditions and confirmation that corresponding adjustments to upstream and downstream Transportation have been made in a manner satisfactory to Company. Such Intraday Nominations can be used to request increases or decreases in total flow or changes to delivery points of scheduled Gas. Any decrease shall be no less than the elapsed, prorated scheduled quantity. A request to increase a nomination for Firm storage service up to the MDIQ and MDWQ specified in the storage service agreement will be accommodated to the extent operating conditions permit. Firm Intraday Nominations other than those submitted during the Intraday 2 Nomination Cycle shall have priority over nominated and scheduled Interruptible volumes. A request to increase a nomination for Interruptible storage shall be permitted at Company's sole discretion and only to the extent that capacity is available and that no displacement of other Interruptible storage service occurs. Such changes will become effective only when system operating conditions permit, as determined by Company.
All nominations, including Intraday Nominations, should be based on a daily quantity; thus, an Intraday Nomination need not be submitted as an hourly nomination. Intraday Nominations do not have roll-over options and will replace the Standing Nomination only for the duration of the Gas Day. Quantities for Intraday Nominations will be expressed in MMBtu, and represent the total quantities to be delivered prior to the end of the effective Gas Day.
16.10 Company shall be allowed to rely conclusively on the information submitted as part of the nomination in confirming the nomination for scheduling and allocation. Customer must provide to Company Customer's current designated contact, after-hours and emergency telephone numbers. Such information must be updated as often as changes to such information occurs. Company may rely solely upon the information provided by Customer and will not be liable to Customer if Customer's contact information is outdated and communication attempts with such Customer are unsuccessful.
16.11 Scheduled quantities will be received and delivered at a uniform hourly rate of scheduled quantity divided by 24. Company shall have the sole discretion to accept variations from such hourly rates.
Article XVII Force Majeure
17.1 The term "force majeure" as employed herein shall mean any cause, whether of the kind enumerated herein or otherwise, not reasonably within the control of Company, such as acts of God; strikes, lockouts and industrial disputes or disturbances; inability to secure or delays in obtaining labor, materials, supplies, permits, easements or rights-of-way, including inability to secure materials by reason of allocations promulgated by authorized governmental agencies; arrests and restraints of governments and people; interruptions by government or court orders; present and future valid orders, decisions or rulings of any government or regulatory entity having proper jurisdiction; acts of the public enemy; vandalism; wars; riots; civil disturbances; blockades; insurrections; epidemics; landslides; lightning; tornadoes, hurricanes; earthquakes; fires; storms; floods; washouts; inclement weather which necessitates extraordinary measures and expense to maintain operations; failure of computer equipment; explosions; breakage, accidents and/or maintenance to plant facilities including machinery, lines of pipe, accidents and/or unscheduled maintenance of wells or subsurface storage caverns or reservoirs; testing (as required by governmental authority or as deemed necessary by Company for the safe operation of the facilities required to perform the services hereunder); and the making of repairs or alterations to pipelines, storage, and plant facilities including Transporter's pipeline repairs. It is understood and agreed that the settlement of strikes or lockouts shall be entirely within the discretion of Company, and that the requirements that any force majeure shall be remedied with all reasonable dispatch shall not require the settlement of strikes or lockouts by acceding to the demands of opposing party when such course is inadvisable in the discretion of Company.
17.2 If either party shall fail to perform any obligation imposed upon it by this Statement of Operating Conditions or by an executed storage service agreement, and such failure shall be caused, or contributed to, by force majeure as described in Paragraph 17.1 above, such failure shall be deemed not to be a breach of the obligation of such party, but such party shall use reasonable diligence to carry out its obligations; provided, however, that no such cause affecting the performance of either party shall continue to relieve such party from its obligation after the expiration of a reasonable period of time within which by the use of due diligence such party could have remedied the situation preventing its performance, nor shall any such cause relieve either party from any obligation unless such party shall give notice thereof in writing to the other party with reasonable promptness; and like notice shall be given upon termination of such cause.
17.3 A force majeure event shall not relieve Customer from its obligations to make payments due, including the payments of reservation charges for the duration of such cause, except as provided in Paragraph 17.4.
17.4 Should a force majeure event render Company unable to satisfy its Firm obligations to Customer for at least seven consecutive days, then Company shall, for the remainder of the force majeure event, waive the applicable reservation charges for the Firm obligations that cannot be satisfied by Company; provided, however, such waiver shall be effective only if (i) mutually acceptable alternative receipt or delivery points are not available, (ii) Customer is not in breach of its service agreement or this Statement of Operating Conditions, and (iii) Customer is not obligated to make payments of reservation charges as set forth immediately below. Should such force majeure event described in this Paragraph 17.4 extend beyond ninety (90) consecutive days, at Company's request Customer shall elect to either (i) resume payments of all reservation charges, or (ii) reduce the MSQ, MDIQ, and/or MDWQ, as applicable, in the storage service agreement by the average daily quantity of Firm obligations for which Company has waived reservation charges during the preceding ninety (90) days, and begin paying reservation charges on such reduced MSQ, MDIQ and/or MDWQ. Any such modification to the storage service agreement shall be in effect for the remaining term of the Transportation service agreement, unless amended by the mutual agreement of both parties.
Article XVIII Gas at End of Term
18.1 At least ten (10) Business Days prior to the expiration of Customer's storage service agreement, Company shall notify Customer of the quantity of Gas held in Customer's Working Gas Inventory. Notice to Customer may be given orally, but shall be confirmed in writing. Customer must either withdraw the Gas or indicate in writing to Company that it desires to have Company cash out the Gas on mutually agreeable terms. If, by midnight on the last Gas Day of Customer's storage service agreement, Customer has neither withdrawn the Gas nor indicated in writing that it desires to exercise the cash out option, then Company may take, free and clear of any adverse claims, title to such quantities as Customer was required to withdraw or cash out; provided, however, that if Customer was unable to withdraw its Gas due to an interruption of Customer's withdrawal service during the last ten Gas Days before termination, Customer shall be allowed to withdraw its Gas within a reasonable period following the end of Customer's storage service agreement.
Article XIX Fuel
19.1 Customer shall furnish, at the Point of Receipt, Gas used for Fuel in an amount up to 0.9% multiplied by the quantities of Gas scheduled to be received by Company from Customer. No Fuel will be assessed upon withdrawal. The assessed percentage of fuel may change from time to time as determined by Company and, if applicable, as approved by the regulatory body having jurisdiction.
19.2 Company may from time to time purchase or sell Gas on an interruptible basis as necessary to manage the Storage Facility pressure and maintain the integrity of the Storage Facility. The purchase or sale of Gas shall be made on a nondiscriminatory basis.
Article XX Billing and Payment
20.1 Not later than the tenth (10th) Business Day of each month, Company shall provide Customer an invoice and any required backup data (which may be transmitted by fax) setting forth (i) the charges due for the preceding month; (ii) the total quantity of Gas, stated in MMBtus, received from and delivered to Customer hereunder during the preceding month(s), with applicable Point of Receipt and Point(s) of Delivery properly identified, and the amount due therefor; and if applicable, (iii) the amount of Customer's Gas in storage as of the close of the preceding month and information sufficient to explain and support any adjustments made by Company in determining the amount billed. If actual quantities are not available by the tenth (10th) Business Day of the month, Company may invoice based on the best available data subject to adjustment to actuals at a later date or Company may delay the issuance of the invoice until actual quantities are available.
20.2 Customer shall pay Company the full amount reflected on the invoice within ten (10) days of its receipt of same. Payments shall be made by wire transfer to the Company account as specified on the invoice provided to Customer. If the tenth (10th) day shall fall upon a weekend or legal holiday, then such payment shall be made on the last regular Business Day prior to such tenth (10th) day. Customer making payment shall submit supporting documentation; Company shall apply payment per supporting documentation provided by Customer; and if payment differs from invoiced amount, remittance detail shall be provided with the payment.
20.3 If an error is discovered in any billing, such error shall be adjusted within thirty (30) days of the determination thereof. If a dispute arises as to the amount payable in any invoice rendered hereunder, Customer shall nevertheless pay when due the amount not in dispute under such invoice. Such payment shall not be deemed to be a waiver of the right by Customer to recoup any overpayment, nor shall acceptance of any payment be deemed to be a waiver of the right by Customer to recoup any overpayment, nor shall acceptance of any payment by Company be deemed to be a waiver by Company of any underpayment. In the event Customer fails to forward the entire undisputed amount due to Company when same is due, interest on the unpaid portion shall accrue at a rate equal to two percent (2%) above the prime rate published in The Wall Street Journal, from time to time, or the maximum legal rate, whichever is the lesser, compounded daily from the date such payment is due until the same is paid. If Customer's failure to pay the undisputed portion of any invoice rendered hereunder continues beyond thirty (30) days after the due date of such invoice, then Company, in addition to all other legal remedies available to it, shall have the right and option to suspend further deliveries of Gas until such default shall have been cured. If Customer's failure to pay the undisputed portion of any invoice rendered hereunder continues beyond sixty (60) days after the due date of such invoice, then Company, in addition to all other legal remedies available to it, shall have the right and option to terminate service hereunder and under the storage service agreement.
20.4 If Customer withholds payment of any disputed amount as authorized herein, Customer shall, within ten (10) days after the due date of the disputed invoice, submit to Company a written explanation of the dispute and any available supporting documentation. The parties shall then cooperate in good faith to resolve such dispute as expeditiously as possible, and the portion, if any, of such disputed amount eventually determined to be due shall bear interest at the rate stated in Paragraph 20.3 above from the original due date until the date actually paid.
20.5 Both Company and Customer shall have the right at their own expense to examine and audit at any reasonable time the books, records (including measurement, billing and payment) and charts of the other to the extent necessary to verify the accuracy of any statements or charges made under or pursuant to any of the provisions of Customer's storage service agreement. Upon request, Customer shall also make available to Company for audit purposes any relevant records of the Transporter to which Customer conveniently has access. A formal audit of accounts shall not be made more often than once each Contract Year. Any inaccuracy will be promptly corrected when discovered; provided, however, that neither Company nor Customer shall be required to maintain books, records or charts for a period of more than two (2) Contract Years following the end of the Contract Year to which they are applicable. Neither Company nor Customer shall have any right to question or contest any charge or credit if the matter is not called to the attention of the other in writing within two (2) years after the end of the Contract Year in question.

Such transfer shall not be effective until approved by the other party. Provided further, either Customer or Company may transfer its interest to any parent or affiliate by assignment, merger or otherwise without the prior approval of the other, but no such transfer shall operate to relieve the transferor of its obligations hereunder. Notwithstanding the foregoing, either party may assign its rights, title, and interest in, and by virtue of the service agreement, including any and all extensions, renewals, amendments, and supplements hereto, to a trustee or trustees, individual or corporate, as security for bonds or other obligations or securities, without such trustee or trustees assuming or becoming in any respect obligated to perform any of the obligations of the assignor and, if any such trustee be a corporation, without its being required by the parties hereto to qualify to do business in the state in which the performance of this agreement may occur. Customer's or Company's transfer in violation of this Paragraph 21.1 shall be void.
